:JOURNEY
Reading Blood Meridian
Section
Impact
- Opening section | 3 | Dense and demanding | No orientation offered, none given
- Desert march | 5 | Extraordinary prose | Where violence and language reach the rare
- Judge Holden | 5 | Most terrifying | The most frightening character in American fiction
- The ending | 4 | Refuses meaning | Right choice for a novel that argues what this does

:NOW
Thinking about No Country for Old Men, which is McCarthy using a similar moral \
frame with more conventional structure, as a companion to this novel.

:NOTE
This is the most violent book I have finished. It is not violent for shock. \
The violence is the argument. Whether that argument is worth engaging with is \
a decision you have to make for yourself.
